#### Current time ​
`Date.now()` and `new Date()` are replaced by deterministic versions that return the time of the last Workflow Task completion.
The value only advances when you `await` something (like `sleep()`):
```
import { sleep } from '@temporalio/workflow';
// Prints the *exact* same timestamp on every iteration
for (let x = 0; x < 10; ++x) {
console.log(Date.now());
}
// Prints timestamps increasing roughly 1s each iteration
for (let x = 0; x < 10; ++x) {
await sleep('1 second');
console.log(Date.now());
}
```

